===[[Etymology]]===
 [It. lava lava, orig. in [[Naples]], a [[torrent]] of [[rain]] overflowing the streets, fr. It. & L. lavare to wash. See [[Lave]].]
===[[Noun]]===
The melted [[rock]] ejected by a [[volcano]] from its top or [[fissure]]d sides. It flows out in streams sometimes miles or kilometres in length. It also issues from fissures in the earth's surface, and forms beds covering many square miles, as in the Northwestern United States. &hand; Lavas are classed, according to their structure, as scoriaceous or cellular, glassy, stony, etc., and according to the material of which they consist, as [[doleritic]], [[trachytic]], etc. Lava [[millstone]], a hard and coarse basaltic millstone from the neighborhood of the [[Rhine]].
